For archived (n = 85) and prospectively collected (n = 46) study specimens combined, the initial agreement between the 2 platforms was 86.4% (kappa = 0.73 [95% CI 0.61–0.84]). After discordant analysis, concordance between FA RP and Nx TAG RPP was demonstrated for 123 of the 131 included specimens, resulting in an overall agreement of 93.9% (kappa = 0.88 [95% CI 0.80–0.96]). In total, FA RP results were not confirmed for 8 specimens after discordant analysis, 4 considered false positives and 4 considered false negatives (Table 2
). The PPA and NPA for all targets in archived and prospectively collected specimens combined were 93.7% (95% CI 83.7–97.7) and 94.1% (95% CI 84.9–98.1), respectively (Table 3
). Overall, there was no significant difference in the performance of the FA RP and NxTAG RPP (McNemar P = 0.72).
